<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'Hail, Golsodix Biroboddle'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Golsodix Biroboddle says 'Hello there Lunal. I must admit that I am not in the highest of spirits on this day. Unless you know something about [Xoomix], please leave me alone.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'Who is Xoomix?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Golsodix Biroboddle says 'Xoomix is a very dear friend of mine that was .. gulp, lost at sea. We were separated when the dastardly Broken Skull Clan overtook our boat. I was the only one that was able to escape, but I fear the worst for my friend. Would you be willing to [help me find Xoomix]?'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'I will help you find Xoomix'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Golsodix Biroboddle says 'You are quite the likeable fellow Lunal. I do appreciate you willing to help me locate where my friend has gone, even if he has passed I would like some proof so that I may sleep easy at night knowing he is at peace. I can begin your search by telling you where our [journey had taken us].'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'Where had your journey taken you?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Golsodix Biroboddle says 'Well you see we were setting sail for the city of Freeport. Xoomix received a few telegrams about some tinkering supplies that were available to him should we be able to travel to Freeport and pick them up. Xoomix was a fantastic tinkerer, he could just about build anything out of nothing. If he should be alive I am sure that he has used his skills to survive. The first place I could ask you to look is around the area of Butcherblock dock. That is where our ship was [overtaken].'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'Who overtook your ship?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Golsodix Biroboddle says 'I do not remember that much from the incident, it happened ever so fast. I do remember how there were many trolls that chanted Glory to the Rok! repeatedly. Perhaps this will aid you in your search. Please return to me with some good news, and please give this clockwork eye to Xoomix should you find him alive. We used to collect them as children so he will definitely know it is from me.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He now gives you an item called A Clockwork Eye that is lore and no drop and identifies as Item Lore: A clockwork eye.  <br>
<br>
Bring this item to Xoomix Haroinoddin in the Gulf of Gunthak.  He is in the lighthouse most of the time but has been seen on the dock as well and other places around the little wharf area by the boat.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'Hail, Xoomix Haroinoddin'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says 'Please. Please help me. I am quite weak and am being [held captive] here against my will.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'Who is holding you captive?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says 'What are you doing?!?! Keep your voice down!  You don't know who I am, you are just another adventurer who will look and feel sorry for me, but will do nothing to help!'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>At this point I handed Xoomix the clockwork eye from Golsodix.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says 'How did you get this? Is it possible that you have come from my friend Golsodix? I am very sorry for yelling at you. You have no idea how being here has broken my spirit. I had almost lost all hope and given up many times, but I knew my friend was out there and would send someone for me. If you can help me escape I will certainly need my [tools].'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'What tools?'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says 'Well, I have many tools that I have either lost while in this place or that were taken from me because the guards thought they had too much value for me to possess them. I also need my gearbox from back home to construct my compass that I need to escape this place. I could set sail anytime I want, but I did not want to risk setting out to sea and dying alone because I didn't know my bearings. If you could [find my possessions] then I could make something that Golsodix would know came from me and he could give you my gearbox.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You say, 'I will find your possessions'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says 'That is great news, Lunal! I will need you to collect four things for me, if you are up to the challenge. My quarterstaff, silvered micro servos, metallic oil and personal toolbox. If you can find these things I can make you something to take to Golsodix. Please return to me with these things when you have found them and make haste because I have grown quite tired being stuck here for so long.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The items he wants drop in Dulak Harbor, except for the metallic oil which drops in Gunthak.  I haven’t seen any of them yet, personally, this information comes from the following posters: Alanya, Caisersoze, Yahtzooba, Kevral, Niella and Jubilex2000.<br>
<br>
-Metallic Oil drops in the pirate fort in Gulf of Gunthak.<br>
<br>
-Xoomix's Toolbox dropped in Dulak off of random mobs apparently (ogres in the NE corner have had it as have mobs near the zoneline). <br>
<br>
-Silvered Micro Servos dropped off the gnomish shipyard architects in Dulak.  This drop is possibly random. <br>
<br>
-Xoomix's Quarterstaff dropped in Dulak off a trollish Gandolak cannoneeron Ganolak's Run (a ship in the harbor).  Possible random drop in zone. <br>
<br>
Take all the items back to Xoomix and boy is he happy to see you!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says &quot;I don't believe it. I never thought I would ever see these tools again. It is quite clear that you intend to help me and for that I am grateful. Here is a quick little something that put together for Golsodix. Bring him this and ask him for my gearbox. Once I have that, I think I can finally get home! Please come back soon!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Now he gives you 'a tinkered contraption' to take back to Golsodix in Ak'anon.  Golsodix is similarly overjoyed when you hand this to him.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Golsodix Biroboddle says &quot;A contraption from Xoomix! I knew he was still alive. This also says that he needs his gearbox to make his compass so he can return home. I must have it here somewhere let me take a look. Ah, here it is. Please take this to Xoomix so he can return home and thank you for all your kind deeds to help a lost gnome. Brell certainly smiles down upon you!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Yay!  A blessing from Brell!  Now one more step to do - he gives you a gearbox to give to Xoomix.  Go back to the Gulf of Gunthak and give it to the gnome.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Xoomix Haroinoddin says &quot;This is it indeed! It has everything I need in here to return home. Please take this charm that I have carried with me for many years. It has brought me good luck throughout my ordeal here and now that I am returning home, I do not think I will need it anymore. Safe travels to you Bretac, I must now ready my boat and finish my compass. May Lord Brell bless you forever!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Break out the beer and pretzels.  For all your farming you are rewarded with a (drumroll, please) charm!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Xoomix's Mystical Charm<br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP <br>
(Str: +8 Mana: +25) <br>
Weight: 0.1<br>
Focus Effect: Extended Range II<br>
Classes: All Classes <br>
Races: All Races <br>
Inventory Slot: Charm</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This charm is Dex-related.  A level 65 wizard with 143 Dex yields 5 Str 8 Mana.  Getting Dex to 213 yielded same stats.  Using Avatar and getting Dex to 305 gave 10 Str 15 Mana and Extended Range II.<br>
<br>
Thanks for everyone who contributed by posting about this quest and its solution.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A> at: 3/11/03 8:05:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=danoduet>DanoDuet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.naturallynovascotia.com/images/noteicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/03 9:55:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=704.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.paralaxguild.com/dano/images/dano_sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Xoomix's Quest</span><hr size=1> anyone have more details on:<br>
